{{This date in recent years}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
* [[563]] &ndash; The Byzantine church [[Hagia Sophia]] in [[Constantinople]] is dedicated for the second time after being destroyed by [[earthquake]]s.
*[[759]] &ndash; [[Tang Dynasty]] poet [[Du Fu]] [[Du Fu#Chengdu|departs for Chengdu]], where he is hosted by fellow poet [[Pei Di]].
*[[1144]] &ndash; The capital of the [[Crusades|crusader]] [[County of Edessa]] [[Siege of Edessa|falls]] to [[Imad ad-Din Zengi]], the [[atabeg]] of [[Mosul]] and [[Aleppo]].
*[[1294]] &ndash; [[Pope Boniface VIII]] is elected [[Pope]], replacing [[Pope Celestine V|St. Celestine V]], who had [[Papal resignation|resigned]].
*[[1777]] &ndash; [[Kiritimati]], also called Christmas Island, is discovered by [[James Cook]].
*[[1814]] &ndash; The [[Treaty of Ghent]] is signed ending the [[War of 1812]].
*[[1818]] &ndash; The first performance of "[[Silent Night]]" takes place in the church of St. Nikolaus in [[Oberndorf bei Salzburg|Oberndorf]], [[Austria]].
*[[1826]] &ndash; The [[Eggnog Riot]] at the [[United States Military Academy]] begins that night, wrapping up the following morning.
*[[1851]] &ndash; [[Library of Congress]] burns.
*[[1865]] &ndash; The [[Ku Klux Klan]] is formed.
*[[1871]] &ndash; [[Aida]] opens in [[Cairo]], [[Egypt]].
*[[1906]] &ndash; [[Radio]]: [[Reginald Fessenden]] transmits the first radio broadcast; consisting of a poetry reading, a [[violin]] solo, and a speech.
*[[1911]] &ndash; [[Lackawanna Cut-Off]] railway line opens in [[New Jersey]] and [[Pennsylvania]].
*[[1913]] &ndash; The [[Italian Hall disaster]] ("1913 Massacre") in [[Calumet, Michigan]], results in the death of 73 Christmas party goers held by striking mine workers, including 59 children.
*[[1914]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: The "[[Christmas truce]]" begins.
*[[1924]] &ndash; [[Albania]] becomes a republic.
*[[1929]] &ndash; Assassination attempt on [[Argentina|Argentine]] President [[Hipólito Yrigoyen]].
*[[1939]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Pope Pius XII]] makes a Christmas Eve appeal for peace.
*[[1941]] &ndash; World War II: [[Kuching]] is conquered by [[Japan]]ese forces.
*[[1942]] &ndash; World War II: [[France|French]] monarchist, [[Fernand Bonnier de La Chapelle]], assassinates [[Vichy]] French Admiral [[François Darlan]] in [[Algiers]], [[Algeria]].
*[[1943]] &ndash; World War II: [[United States|U.S.]] General [[Dwight D. Eisenhower]] becomes the [[Supreme Allied Commander]].
*[[1951]] &ndash; [[Libya]] becomes independent from [[Italy]]. [[Idris of Libya|Idris I]] is proclaimed King of Libya.
*[[1953]] &ndash; [[Tangiwai disaster]]: On [[New Zealand]]'s North Island, at Tangiwai, a railway bridge is damaged by a [[lahar]] and collapses beneath a passenger train, killing 151 people.
*[[1955]] &ndash; [[NORAD Tracks Santa]] for the first time in what will become an annual [[Christmas Eve]] tradition.
*[[1964]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: [[Viet Cong]] operatives [[1964 Brinks Hotel bombing|bomb the Brinks Hotel]] in [[Ho Chi Minh City|Saigon]], [[South Vietnam]] to demonstrate they can strike an American installation in the heavily guarded capital.
*[[1966]] &ndash; A [[Canadair CL-44]] chartered by the [[United States Armed Forces|United States military]] crashes into a small village in [[South Vietnam]], killing 129.
*[[1968]] &ndash; [[Apollo program]]: The crew of ''[[Apollo 8]]'' enters into orbit around the [[Moon]], becoming the first humans to do so. They performed 10 lunar orbits and broadcast live TV pictures that became the famous [[Apollo 8 Genesis reading|Christmas Eve Broadcast]], one of the most watched programs in history.
*[[1969]] &ndash; [[Charles Manson]] is allowed to defend himself at the Tate-LaBianca murder [[trial]].
*[[1972]] &ndash; [[Japan Airlines Flight 472 (1972)|Japan Airlines Flight 472]], operated [[Douglas DC-8|Douglas DC-8-53]] landed at [[Juhu Aerodrome]] instead of [[Chhatrapati Shivaji International Airport|Santacruz Airport]] in [[Mumbai|Bombay]], [[India]].
*[[1973]] &ndash; [[District of Columbia Home Rule Act]] is passed, allowing residents of [[Washington, D.C.]] to elect their own local government.
*[[1974]] &ndash; [[Cyclone Tracy]] devastates [[Darwin, Northern Territory|Darwin, Australia]].
*[[1979]] &ndash; The first [[Europe]]an [[Ariane (rocket family)|Ariane]] rocket is launched.
*[[1980]] &ndash; Witnesses report the first of several sightings of [[Rendlesham Forest incident|unexplained lights]] near [[RAF Woodbridge]], in [[Rendlesham Forest]], [[Suffolk]], [[England]], [[United Kingdom]], an incident called "Britain's [[Roswell UFO incident|Roswell]]".
*[[1994]] &ndash; [[Air France Flight 8969]] is hijacked on the ground, over the course of 3 days 3 passengers are killed, as are all 4 terrorists.
*[[1997]] &ndash; The [[Sid El-Antri massacre]] (or Sidi Lamri) in [[Algeria]] kills 50-100 people.
*[[2000]] &ndash; The [[Texas Seven]] hold up a sports store in [[Irving, Texas]]. Police officer Aubrey Hawkins is murdered during the robbery.
*[[2003]] &ndash; The [[Spain|Spanish]] police thwart an attempt by [[ETA]] to detonate 50&nbsp;kg of [[Explosive material|explosive]]s at 3:55 p.m. inside [[Madrid]]'s busy [[Madrid Chamartín railway station|Chamartín Station]].
*[[2005]] &ndash; [[Chad–Sudan relations]]: [[Chad]] declares a [[Declaration of war|state of war]] against [[Sudan]] following a [[December 18]] [[Battle of Adré|attack on Adré]], which left about 100 people dead.
*[[2008]] &ndash; [[Lord's Resistance Army]], a [[Uganda]]n rebel group, begins a [[2008 Christmas massacres|series of attacks]] on [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], massacring more than 400.

